{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Valid}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

Objects may become invalid via import, unchecked conversions, overlays, etc.

The '''Valid''' [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] can be used with an object of any scalar type (that is, numeric or enumeration types) to know whether its value is valid (e.g. not out-of-range, etc.). The result is always True or False; neither Constraint_Error nor any other [[Ada Programming/Exceptions|exception]] are ever raised.

It is important that the evaluation of the attribute does not count as reading the object, whereas reading an invalid object makes the program erroneous.

== Example ==

 {{Ada/--|Declare a discrete type and explicitly set the position numbers}}
 {{Ada/kw|type}} My_Enum {{Ada/kw|is}} (Value1, Value2, Value3);
 {{Ada/kw|for}} My_Enum {{Ada/kw|use}} (Value1 => 2, Value2 => 4, Value3 => 6 );

 Result             : Natural;
 Enum_Var, Other_Var: My_Enum;
 Sneaky_Back_Door   : Integer;
 {{Ada/kw|for}} Enum_Var'[[Ada Programming/Attributes/'Address|Address]] {{Ada/kw|use}} Sneaky_Back_Door'[[Ada Programming/Attributes/'Address|Address]];

 ...

 {{Ada/kw|if}} {{Ada/kw|not}} Result'{{Ada/attribute|Valid}} {{Ada/kw|then}}
    {{Ada/--|Result is out-of-range, it has a negative value}}
    Result := Natural'{{Ada/attribute|First}};
 {{Ada/kw|end}} {{Ada/kw|if}};
 ...
 {{Ada/--|Assign a bad integer value to the enumerated type variable.}}
 Sneaky_Back_Door := 1;
 Other_Var := Enum_Var;  {{Ada/--|reading Enum_Var makes the program erroneous}}
 ...
 {{Ada/kw|if}} {{Ada/kw|not}} Enum_Var'{{Ada/attribute|Valid}} {{Ada/kw|then}}  {{Ada/--|this is not reading}}
    {{Ada/--|Enum_Var contains a bad value}}
    Enum_Var := My_Enum'{{Ada/attribute|First}};
 {{Ada/kw|end}} {{Ada/kw|if}};

Note that in the erroneous assignment statement above, no range check is performed (hence no exception will be raised) since both variables are of the same subtype.

== See also ==

=== Wikibook ===

* [[Ada Programming]]
* [[Ada Programming/Attributes]]

=== Ada Reference Manual ===

* {{Ada/RM|13|9|2|title=The Valid Attribute}}

=== Ada Quality and Style Guide ===

* {{Ada/SG3|5|9|1|Unchecked Conversion}} &mdash; Consider using the 'Valid attribute to check the validity of scalar data.
* {{Ada/SG3|5|9|7|Direct_IO and Sequential_IO}} &mdash; Use the 'Valid attribute to check the validity of scalar values obtained through Ada.Direct_IO and Ada.Sequential_IO.
* {{Ada/SG3|6|3|3|The Abort Statement}} &mdash; In the presence of the abort statement, consider using the 'Valid attribute to check the validity of scalar data.

=== Ada Rationale ===

* {{Ada/95/R3|part=3|h|1|1|The Valid Attribute}}


