[[../Pericycle/]] is located between the [[../Vasculature|vascular tissues]] and the [[../Endodermis|endodermis]]. It is involved in loading/unloading of vasculature (ref ??).
This tissue has two subpopulation of cells: * cells in front of xylem poles (also called Pericycle Founder Cells, PFCs) are blocked in G2 phase and are able to reenter the cell cycle to [[../Lateral root development|initiate lateral roots]] (Beeckman et al 2001). This tissue is therefore considered as an "extended meristem". * cells in front of phloem poles are not able to initiate lateral roots.
{{BookCat}}

*[[/Cabin/]]
*[[/Engine/]]

{{BookCat}}

There should be six deck vents on a 28 Express. Two face forward, and four face aft. Ducts should be attached to each running to a low point in the bilge. If no where else, a duct should be attached to the bilge blower, and run to a low point to ensure that any gas fumes are drawn out.

While underway, the bilge blower need not be run because the four aft-facing vents will cause suction exhaust while the two forward-facing vents supply intake pressure.

